column1: # The ISC-GEM Global Instrumental Earthquake Catalogue contains:
# Direct sources of scalar moments are currently gcmt (from the GCMT project
# a dedicated webpage (http://www.isc.ac.uk/iscgem/mw_bibliography.php) provides the references used.
# The Supplement to the Catalogue is provided in a separate file. The Supplement
# contains a list of those earthquakes for which poor data availability
# prevented the authors from performing a reliable determination of either
# the epicentre or the magnitude parameters or both.
# Version 2.0  Released on 2015-01-19 (period covered: 1900-2011; added Mw>=~5.5 during 1950-1959 & 2010-2011)
# Version 2.01 Released on 2015-07-10 (period covered: 1900-2011; removed evid = 877612 from the main catalogue as the event is a documented nuclear explosion in Novaya Zemlya)

# Version 3.0  Released on 2016-01-28 (period covered: 1900-2012; added Mw>=~5.5 during 1935-1949 & 2012; reassessed the magnitudes of ~630 existing earthquakes during 1935-1949; relocated further 92 earthquakes outside the period 1935-1949)

# Version 4.0  Released on 2017-01-26 (period covered: 1900-2013; added Mw>=~5.5 during 1920-1934 & 2013; reassessed the magnitudes of ~700 existing earthquakes during 1920-1934; relocated or re-assessed magnitude of 16 earthquakes outside the period 1920-1934)

# Version 5.0  Released on 2018-02-27 (period covered: 1904-2014; dropped the pre-1904 events for lack of station data; processed 1110 new events during 1904-1919 & added 521 events in 2014 with Mw>=~5.5; reassessed location and magnitudes of ~150 existing earthquakes during 1904-1919; relocated or re-assessed magnitude of 7 earthquakes outside the 1904-1919 period)
# Version 5.1  Released on 2018-06-18 (period covered: 1904-2014; added 17 earthquakes between 1933 and 1949 and updated location and/or magnitude of 13 earthquakes)

# Version 6.0  Released on 2019-03-07 (period covered: 1904-2015; added 7012 earthquakes between 1964-1979 AND 2000-2014. These earthquakes include continental events with magnitude 5-5.5 and global events around magnitude 5.5 not selected in previous versions.
